Google is improving its hotel search service on smartphones, which includes better price filtering and the ability to book right from Google. The company is also rolling out new features on mobile search to make it easier for users to look at their travel options when on the go. “In the next few days, you’ll see that if you search for a flight in Google Flights, you can click right in to Hotels at the top of the page,” said Google. “This lets you easily click over to check hotel availability and prices in your destination city for the dates you’ve already selected.” The inverse is also available, where users who searched for a hotel can to the Flights tab to check prices and fare options, and book a flight.